Do you want to write code that actually saves lives?

At Acusensus, we are building the future of road worker protection. We are looking for a Graduate Machine Learning Engineer to join a truly greenfield project, helping us design and deploy advanced technology that protects workers in high-risk environments globally.

WHO WE ARE & WHY YOU'LL LOVE WORKING WITH US

At Forsite, a division of Acusensus, we're not just building technology; we're building a shield. Every day, roadside and infrastructure workers put themselves at risk to keep our communities moving. Our Forsite division is on a mission to transform their safety.

We have a clear, vital goal: Every worker connected, every worker protected.

This is not a "cog in the wheel" role. Under the mentorship of senior engineers, you will help shape core architecture, build ML tooling, and deploy production-grade algorithms that power real-time hazard detection.

WHAT YOU'LL BE DOING

As a Graduate ML Engineer, you will work end-to-end across data, models, and edge deployment. You won't just be tweaking parameters; you will be getting your hands dirty with real-world sensor data, deep learning models, and NVIDIA Jetson hardware.

Key Responsibilities:

Model Development: Design, train, and evaluate deep learning models (PyTorch) for real-time object detection, tracking, and classification.
Algorithm Design: Implement algorithms for trajectory estimation, vehicle motion analysis, and sensor fusion (Cameras, Radar, GNSS).
Data Pipeline: Support the full lifecycle—collecting, labelling, cleaning, and organising datasets.
Edge Deployment: Help build reproducible workflows to export models (e.g., ONNX) and deploy them to edge environments.
Field Validation: Participate in lab and field testing to prove your code works in the real world, not just on a server.

WHAT YOU’LL BRING

We are looking for a high-potential graduate who combines strong academic foundations with a "builder" mindset. You should be someone who takes ownership of a problem rather than waiting for instructions.

Essential Qualifications & Skills:

Education: Recently completed (or nearing completion) a degree in CS, Software Engineering, Mechatronics, Data Science, or related fields.
Strong Academics: A solid foundation in Linear Algebra, Probability, and Statistics (High distinction/80+ average in these subjects is a key criterion).
Technical Stack: Strong programming skills in Python and C++.
ML & Frameworks: Hands-on experience with PyTorch (preferred) or TensorFlow, with specific exposure to Computer Vision.
Ownership: Demonstrated initiative to solve problems independently (e.g., through capstone projects, internships, or open-source work).

Nice to Have:

Experience with NVIDIA Jetson or embedded systems.
Knowledge of MLOps (Docker, CI/CD, ONNX Runtime).
Familiarity with C# or safety-critical systems.

YOUR WORKING ENVIRONMENT

This is a full-time, hybrid role, based in our Ingleburn office, NSW. At Acusensus, we trust our team to work in ways that maximise productivity, collaboration, and well-being, while staying connected to our mission of making roads safer.

WHY YOU'LL LOVE WORKING WITH US

Impact: Your code will directly contribute to keeping road workers safe.

Mentorship: Work directly alongside and learn from experienced Machine Learning Engineers.

Greenfield Innovation: This is a rare chance to work on a product from the early stages, influencing its architecture and design.

Flexibility: We are based in Ingleburn with hybrid working options to support your work-life balance.

A Culture of Delivery: We value collaboration, integrity, and care. We're a team that plans, forecasts, and delivers

READY TO MAKE A DIFFERENCE? APPLY NOW.

Visit www.acusensus.com.au/careers or submit your application directly through this advertisement. If you have any questions or would like to discuss the role in greater detail, please email careers@acusensus.com.

Application Process

In your application, please include the following items:

1. Initial Application

Upload your most recent Resume

Upload your Academic Transcript of completed units. Please upload this to the 'Certifications and Licenses' section

Answers to a short list of questions (You will be asked these once you create your account and apply)

2. Interviews:

Initial pre-screening call.

Stage 1 Interview - technical. W/C 12 Jan 2026

Stage 2 Interview.

3. Assessment & Offer:

Pre-employment screening, including Police and Driver History checks

Offer Letter

Acusensus is building a diverse and inclusive workplace where everyone feels valued, respected, and empowered to drive positive change. We’re committed to fostering an environment where creativity and authenticity are celebrated. No matter your background, if you’re passionate about making a difference, we encourage you to apply.

Position Summary:

The Analytics Engineer at MYMC is responsible for developing and maintaining a robust, scalable data infrastructure, ensuring data accuracy and accessibility to support advanced analytics, automation, and AI initiatives across the organisation.

This role collaborates with Engineering, Product, Marketing, Operations, and Finance to transform raw data into reliable, reusable assets that inform decision-making and enhance business processes.

Key Responsibilities but not limited too:

Data foundations and modelling

Build and maintain clean, well-modelled datasets that support analytics, automation, and AI use cases.
Own core transformation logic across customer, order, subscription, marketing, and operational data.
Design data models that prioritise consistency, reusability, and long-term maintainability over one-off outputs.

Data quality, reliability & trust

Implement automated data quality checks, monitoring, and alerting.
Identify root causes of data issues and fix them at the source.
Establish and uphold standards for testing, documentation, naming, and version control.

Enablement & Self Service

Create datasets and semantic layers that allow teams to self-serve confidently without constant data team involvement.
Reduce reliance on bespoke queries and manual data extracts.
Partner with stakeholders to interpret results and drive action.

Advanced analytics and automation:

Design and deliver analytical models where needed.
Translate business problems into analytical approaches, not just queries.
Identify opportunities to automate recurring analysis or decision logic.

Skills & Experience:

Essential

Strong SQL skills, with experience building analytical data models.
Experience with ELT/ETL pipelines and modern data stacks.
Hands-on experience with cloud data platforms (Databricks, Azure preferred).
Strong understanding of data quality, testing, and maintainability.
Ability to work autonomously and make pragmatic trade-offs.
Clear communication skills and comfort partnering with non-technical teams.

Desirable:

Python experience for transformations, automation, or data quality tooling.
Experience supporting analytics for ecommerce, subscriptions, or marketing.
Exposure to dbt-style modelling patterns.
Experience preparing data for ML or advanced analytics use cases.
Familiarity with Power BI (but not defined by it).
Experience with Dynamics 365 data.

Next Steps:

Applications open for review from 7 January 2025, and we’ll be in touch with shortlisted candidates shortly after, from 12 January 2025 onward.

VALE Partners have been engaged by an innovative, data-driven technology company to find their next Senior Data Engineer. You'll be joining a fully-remote team on a mission to build a world-class data platform that will transform their industry.

Job Title: Cloud and AI Solution Architect - Infrastructure - Sydney/Brisbane
Ad Text:
Overview


Bring your cloud and AI engineering talent to our team and shape Australia’s future as you architect Azure Infrastructure at scale for major retailers and public sector organisations, innovating and powering the services Australians use every day.

 Microsoft’s mission is to empower every person and every organisation on the planet to achieve more. We bring this mission to life through a growth mindset, a culture built on respect, integrity, and accountability, and an environment where every individual can thrive.

 The Customer Experience and Success (CE&S) organisation exists to help customers realise business value faster through differentiated customer experiences powered by Microsoft technology. Our people play a central role in delivering these outcomes by guiding organisations through complex cloud transformation journeys.

As a CE&S Cloud and AI Solution Architect specialising in Infrastructure, you will support the technical relationship between Microsoft and your customers, helping them adopt Microsoft Azure infrastructure services in a secure, scalable, and effective way. You will contribute to architecture design, modernisation activities, hybrid cloud adoption, and operational optimisation under the guidance of senior technical leaders.

This role is ideal for someone early in their cloud architecture career who enjoys hands‑on technology, learning from senior Cloud and AI Solution Architects, and building confidence in customer‑facing delivery. You will work on meaningful Azure Infrastructure workloads across Australia and New Zealand while developing deeper technical and consulting capability over time.

You will be supported by a team of like‑minded peers who will help you grow your technical depth and deliver innovative Azure solutions for major retailers and public sector organisations.

This role can be based in either Brisbane or Sydney.

Flexible work arrangements are supported in this role.

If you meet most but not all the requirements, we encourage you to apply. We welcome applicants who are still building confidence, our team values diverse perspectives and potential as much as experience.

Responsibilities

Infrastructure Architecture Support & Delivery

Support design and implementation of Microsoft Azure Infrastructure solutions across compute, networking, storage, identity, and hybrid connectivity.

Assist in modernising on‑premises systems, migrating workloads, configuring hybrid architectures, and improving operational readiness.

Apply “well‑architected” principles to ensure foundational security, reliability, cost optimisation and performance.

Work closely with senior Cloud and AI Solution Architects to validate designs, troubleshoot issues, and ensure delivery quality.

Technical Learning, Depth, and Contribution

Build foundational expertise in:

Microsoft Azure Infrastructure‑as‑a‑Service

Identity and access management with Microsoft Entra ID

Virtual networks, firewalls, and hybrid connectivity

Backup, disaster recovery, and business continuity

Automation, monitoring, and governance basics

Complete priority technical certifications and develop proficiency across selected Infrastructure workloads.

Contribute to shared learning by capturing insights, documenting approaches, and participating in community knowledge‑sharing.

Customer and Partner Interaction

Support customer conversations by gathering requirements, preparing technical materials, and contributing to and delivering solution recommendations.

Assist senior Cloud and AI Solution Architects in delivering architecture sessions, troubleshooting challenges, and guiding customers through early adoption steps.

Collaborate with partner organisations on implementation activities, under direction from senior technical leads.

Operational Excellence

Practice consistent documentation hygiene, delivery tracking, and adherence to Microsoft methodologies.

Participate in internal learning communities, readiness programs, and technical enablement activities.

Reflect customer feedback and insights back into internal engineering and support channels.

Qualifications
Required Qualifications

Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, Engineering, Business, or related field AND at least 2 years of experience in:

Cloud or Infrastructure technologies,

Information technology consulting or support,

Systems administration,

Network operations,

Software development or support,

Technical solution delivery or architecture.
OR equivalent experience without a formal degree.

 Preferred Qualifications

Hands‑on experience supporting cloud or hybrid infrastructure implementations, including basic design, configuration, or troubleshooting.

Exposure to Microsoft Azure, Amazon Web Services, or other cloud environments.

Understanding of networking, operating systems, identity, and security fundamentals.

Demonstrated client-facing communication skills with the desire to grow into customer‑facing architectural leadership.

Curiosity, adaptability, and willingness to learn from senior Cloud Solution Architects.

Ability to organise work, follow guidance, and contribute to well‑structured delivery.


This position will be open for a minimum of 5 days, with applications accepted on an ongoing basis until the position is filled.

Microsoft is an equal opportunity employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to age, ancestry, citizenship, color, family or medical care leave, gender identity or expression, genetic information, immigration status, marital status, medical condition, national origin, physical or mental disability, political affiliation, protected veteran or military status, race, ethnicity, religion, sex (including pregnancy), sexual orientation, or any other characteristic protected by applicable local laws, regulations and ordinances. If you need assistance with religious accommodations and/or a reasonable accommodation due to a disability during the application process, read more about requesting accommodations.

Ad Text:
Overview

Bring your cloud and AI engineering talent to our team and shape Australia’s future as you architect Azure Infrastructure at scale for major retailers and public sector organisations, innovating and powering the services Australians use every day.

 Microsoft’s mission is to empower every person and every organisation on the planet to achieve more. We bring this mission to life through a growth mindset, a culture built on respect, integrity, and accountability, and an environment where every individual can thrive.

 The Customer Experience and Success (CE&S) organisation exists to help customers realise business value faster through differentiated customer experiences powered by Microsoft technology. Our people play a central role in delivering these outcomes by guiding organisations through complex cloud transformation journeys.

 As a CE&S Cloud and AI Solution Architect specialising in Infrastructure, you will own the end‑to‑end technical relationship with customers and guide their adoption of Microsoft Azure infrastructure services in the most effective way. You will design secure, scalable, resilient architecture patterns and lead customers through modernisation, optimisation, migration, and hybrid cloud deployments. You will connect customer needs with the right Azure capabilities and create sustainable, high‑quality outcomes that accelerate their cloud journey.

Infrastructure Architecture and Delivery Leadership

Lead architectural design and implementation planning for Microsoft Azure Infrastructure workloads, including compute, networking, identity, security, storage, and hybrid connectivity.

Guide customers through modernisation of legacy systems, on‑premises migrations, hybrid cloud integrations, disaster recovery strategy, and virtualisation optimisation.

Apply “well‑architected” principles to ensure solutions are secure, resilient, high‑performing, maintainable, and cost‑optimised.

Collaborate with engineering teams, partner organisations, and technical leaders to remove blockers and ensure successful deployment of Infrastructure‑as‑a‑Service solutions.

Maintain deep expertise in:

Microsoft Azure Infrastructure‑as‑a‑Service

Identity and access management (including Microsoft Entra ID)

Hybrid networking and network security

Disaster recovery, backup, and business continuity design

Virtualisation (Microsoft Azure VMware Solution, Hyper‑V), container hosting, and automation

Infrastructure governance, monitoring, and operations

Create reusable intellectual property such as scripts, templates, automation, design patterns, and repeatable frameworks.

Provide technical leadership in architecture reviews and customer technology strategy discussions.

 Customer and Partner Engagement

Act as a trusted advisor by understanding customer business challenges and shaping Infrastructure architecture recommendations that deliver clear business value.

Build senior stakeholder relationships to influence cloud strategy and drive adoption decisions.

Partner with Microsoft service providers and systems integrators to scale Infrastructure solution delivery.

 Operational Excellence and Leadership Impact

Apply disciplined documentation, milestone hygiene, planning, and delivery practices aligned to Microsoft methodologies.

Mentor early‑in‑career Cloud Solution Architects and contribute to capability uplift across the Infrastructure community.

Share best practices, patterns, and technical learnings with peers and v‑teams.


Qualifications

Required Qualifications

Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, Engineering, Business, or a related field AND 4–6 years of hands‑on experience in:

Systems administration,

Cloud or hybrid environment management,

Technical consulting,

Infrastructure automation or solution delivery.
OR equivalent professional experience.

At least 3 years of experience designing or implementing Microsoft Azure Infrastructure solutions or Infrastructure solutions on another major cloud platform.

Demonstrated ability to influence technical decisions with senior customer stakeholders.

 Preferred Qualifications

5+ years of experience working across cloud or hybrid infrastructure environments, including migration, networking, identity, security, and storage.

Experience with enterprise‑scale architecture patterns, Infrastructure‑as‑Code automation, monitoring, and governance practices.

Hands‑on experience designing hybrid architectures involving on‑premises systems, Microsoft Azure VMware Solution, and connected network environments.

Ability to communicate complex Infrastructure concepts clearly to both technical and non‑technical audiences.

Experience contributing reusable frameworks, automation, or technical guidance.

Demonstrated problem‑solving capability, comfort with ambiguity, and ability to lead multi‑disciplinary teams.

This position will be open for a minimum of 5 days, with applications accepted on an ongoing basis until the position is filled.

About the position

Sightline Intelligence - Murarrie, Brisbane 

Are you a senior ML engineer ready to step into a hands-on management role who thrives on both leading technical direction and staying deeply technical? Sightline Intelligence, a leader in Defence AI and Computer Vision, is seeking a capable technical leader to help shape and deliver mission-critical perception systems deployed at the tactical edge. 

In this role, you will collaborate with engineering leadership to define goals and scope, translate operational requirements into actionable plans, and drive the execution of complex ML initiatives. You will act as a trusted technical authority for customers and internal teams while still contributing significant hands-on modelling, data, optimisation, and deployment work. 

If you're looking for a hands-on leadership role with real impact - this is it!

About Sightline Intelligence

Sightline Intelligence (formerly Athena Artificial Intelligence) is a highly innovative Defence technology company delivering game-changing capabilities to international clients. Sightline Intelligence is one of the only companies providing vision-based AI systems to the Australian Defence industry that combines computer vision, AI enabled geospatial data analytics and AI augmented decision support to the connected battlefield. Our systems are deployed in real operational environments, supporting real missions with real consequences. 


Key Responsibilities:

Hands-On Machine Learning & Computer Vision  

Design, train, evaluate, and iterate on object detection, classification, and segmentation models for operational use. 

Run structured experimentation, ablations, and performance analysis to guide architecture and design decisions. 

Optimise and convert models for edge deployment (TensorRT, ONNX, TFLite, QNN), balancing accuracy, latency, and system constraints. 

Contribute to data strategy and implementation, including ingestion, curation, quality filtering, annotation workflows, and dataset versioning. 

Benchmark, profile, and tune performance on embedded targets (Jetson, Qualcomm) and support integration into mission systems. 

Define and maintain ML system assurance practices, including verification and validation criteria, performance baselines, and regression checks. 

Produce clear technical documentation covering system architecture, model behaviour, assumptions, and limitations to support auditability and operational confidence. 

Technical Leadership, Strategy & Management  

Work with engineering leadership to define technical goals, scope work, and align ML development with program and customer objectives. 

Act as a senior technical interface for customers and stakeholders, supporting requirements definition, design trade-offs, progress reviews, and technical briefings. 

Take accountability for ML team delivery, quality, and outcomes, acting as an advocate for the team across engineering, program, and customer forums. 

Establish and uphold engineering standards for ML development, including code quality, testing, CI pipelines, system integration, and release readiness. 

Design and document ML-enabled systems to ensure robustness, assurance, reliability, and operational suitability, producing clear artefacts to support auditability and compliance. 

Stay current with state-of-the-art ML, computer vision, and AI assurance practices, guiding adoption of best-in-class methods and tools. 

Build and grow the ML team through mentoring, recruitment, onboarding, and ongoing capability development. 

Qualifications

Required 

Bachelor’s, Master’s, or equivalent experience in Computer Science, Engineering, Data Science, or a related field. 

Significant professional experience delivering production machine learning systems, with a strong emphasis on computer vision. 

Demonstrated hands-on expertise in deep learning model development and deployment using frameworks such as PyTorch. 

Ability to design, document, and reason about ML-enabled systems, including assurance, validation, and operational considerations. 

Excellent communication skills, including the ability to work with customers and explain technical decisions clearly. 

Strong data engineering fundamentals (NumPy, pandas, scikit-learn). 

Australian citizenship and the ability to obtain an Australian Government Security Clearance. 

Highly Desirable 

Prior experience in a senior, lead, or managerial ML role while remaining hands-on. 

Experience recruiting, mentoring, or building ML engineering teams. 

Experience deploying models on embedded edge platforms (NVIDIA Jetson, Qualcomm). 

Familiarity with MLOps tooling, CI/CD pipelines, experiment tracking systems, and workflow automation. 

Exposure to Defence, robotics, aerospace, or other safety/mission critical real-time system constraints. 

Awareness of contemporary best practices in trustworthy AI, model assurance, and system-level validation. 

Why Sightline Intelligence?

Cutting-Edge Projects: Work on real-world, high-impact AI applications at the forefront of defence innovation. 

Technical Leadership: Influence architecture, tooling, and the direction of ML capability. 

Hands-On Engineering: Stay deeply technical while leading and mentoring others. 

Competitive Compensation: Strong salary and benefits package. 

Brisbane Location: Work at our Murarrie office - close to the CBD without the daily gridlock. 

We encourage candidates with diverse backgrounds and experiences to apply, even if you feel you may not meet all the selection criteria. At Sightline Intelligence, we value the unique perspectives and skills that each candidate can bring to our team. 

Note that due to the nature of our projects, you MUST BE AN AUSTRALIAN CITIZEN to be considered for this position. Our roles require an Australian Government Security Clearance, or the ability to obtain one. Security clearances may only be granted to Australian citizens. Applicants who accept a conditional offer of employment may be subject to government security investigation(s) and must meet eligibility requirements for access to classified information. 

We look forward to reviewing your application and potentially welcoming you to our innovative and passionate team!

Job Title: Principal Machine Learning Systems Engineer, Search Engineering
Ad Text:
Working at Atlassian


Atlassians can choose where they work – whether in an office, from home, or a combination of the two. That way, Atlassians have more control over supporting their family, personal goals, and other priorities. We can hire people in any country where we have a legal entity.

Your Future Team


Search Platform powers the search functionality in Atlassian products. The team delivers low-latency, highly relevant, and reliable search experiences for all Atlassian users across all surfaces by supporting scalable runtime systems, query orchestration, and robust serving infrastructure. It ensures fast, accurate results for every query.

As Atlassian's client base and content volume grow, search becomes an increasingly challenging engineering domain.

About the Role


As a Principal Machine Learning Systems Engineer, you’ll be at the intersection of search, machine learning and experimentation. You will work directly with cross-functional teams to deliver innovative, ML-powered solutions that directly impact millions of customers.

This job requires strong software engineering skills: 70% engineering and 30% machine learning. In this role, you'll get the chance to:

Regularly tackle the largest and most complex problems on the team, from technical design to launch

Determine plans-of-attack on large projects

Solve complex architecture challenges and apply architectural standards

Develop and deploy ranking models to optimize ranking to improve the user experience and achieve business objectives

Develop robust feature engineering practices to ingest, process, and serve features for offline training and online inference at scale.

Architect and optimize data infrastructure for ingesting, processing, and serving large-scale, high-velocity search and experimentation data.

Oversee the end-to-end deployment of ML solutions into production, ensuring continuous evaluation, monitoring, and improvement.

Transfer your depth of knowledge from your current language to excel as a Software Engineer

Lead code reviews & documentation and take on complex bug fixes, especially on high-risk problems

Partner across engineering teams to take on company-wide programmes in multiple projects

Mentor and guide junior engineers, fostering a culture of innovation, collaboration, and continuous learning.

Communicate complex technical concepts clearly to both technical and non-technical stakeholders, creating concise artifacts for peers, partners, and leadership.

Your Background


On the first day we will expect you to have

10+ years experience in multiple hands-on software/technology leadership roles, with end-to-end responsibility through the software development lifecycle

Experience with ML workflows and observability at scale.

Proven track record of tech-leading AI/ML products from conception to launch.

Bachelor/Master/PHD with a preference for Computer Science degree

Expertise with one or more prominent languages such as Java, Python, Kotlin, Go, or TypeScript is required.

Understanding of SaaS, PaaS, IaaS industry with hands-on experience with public cloud offerings (e.g., AWS, GCP, or Azure)

Knowledge to evaluate trade-offs between correctness, robustness, performance, space and time

Practice in mentoring other engineers and influencing decision makers throughout the organisation

Consider the customer impact when making technical decisions

If you've got these skills, even better

Experience in OpenSearch, Elasticsearch, or other search engine technologies

Experience in Developer Experience or Developer Productivity

Experience in Online and Offline experimentation

Proficiency in Java, Python

Experience in CI (Continuous Integration) and CD (Continuous Deployment)

2+ years of experience running search systems at scale.

Benefits & Perks


Atlassian offers a wide range of perks and benefits designed to support you, your family and to help you engage with your local community. Our offerings include health and wellbeing resources, paid volunteer days, and so much more. To learn more, visit go.atlassian.com/perksandbenefits.

About Atlassian

IDEA Bio based at the Australian Institute for Bioengineering and Nanotechnology (AIBN)
Full-time (100%), fixed-term position for up to 2 years

About This Opportunity

We are seeking a software engineer to aid the LEARN team at IDEA Bio in establishing a data analysis pipeline. In this unique role, you will work closely with data scientists, a bioinformatician and a machine learning specialist to construct custom workflows that allow the high-throughput processing and analysis of data from a Laboratory Information Management System.

Key responsibilities will include:

Core Scientific

Contribute to the coding and development of custom data analysis algorithms and modelling tools for systems biology or machine-learning.
Develop a flexible, modular data analysis pipeline that retrieves data from a LIMS system (OpenBIS), performs required pre-processing and quality checks and prepares data for analysis through custom and open-source tools and workflows to analyse data as required by the LEARN team.
Ensure said pipeline is deployable and operable on high-performance computing.
Where relevant, re-code existing software into more appropriate languages or to enhance performance.
Develop flowcharts, layouts and documentation to identify requirements and solutions.
Write well-designed, testable code.
Develop software verification plans and quality assurance procedures.
Document and maintain software functionality.
Use an appropriate repository, primarily GitHub, to share software and enable collaborative development with other researchers.
Where required, maintain or further develop the data and metadata capture workflows that capture bioreactor and sample data in the LIMS system.
Contribute to research outputs, joint preparation, and authorship of reports/manuscripts as appropriate.
If relevant, contribute to the set-up and operation of cloud-based bioreactor systems.

General

Perform other duties as reasonably directed by the Senior Data Scientist.

Safety

Ensure a high standard of occupational health and safety standards and systems, including inductions, supervision, equipment training registers, administration of research facilities, inventories, reporting and investigating injuries, incidents, and hazards.

Leadership and management

Promptly resolve conflict and grievances when they arise in accordance with University policy and procedures.
About the Integrated Designed Environment for Advanced Biomanufacturing (IDEA Bio)

IDEA Bio has emerged as a state-of-the-art fermentation biofoundry, dedicated to providing high-quality services to both academic and industry partners. Our mission is to develop sustainable bioprocesses that contribute to the growth of Queensland's bioeconomy and enhance Australia's position in the global biotechnology landscape. IDEA Bio is composed of a TEST capability, involving the culturing of organisms in bioreactors and gathering data about fermentation performance and cell physiology (including 'omics measurements such as protein and metabolite measurements), and a LEARN capability, that seeks to use these large data sets to learn how to alter fermentation parameters or genetically engineer strains to enhance performance. We also collaborate closely with Queensland Metabolomics and Proteomics (Q MAP https://www.qmap.org.au/) and the Australian Genome Foundry (Macquarie University).

About UQ

As part of the UQ community, you will have the opportunity to work alongside the brightest minds, who have joined us from all over the world.

Everyone here has a role to play. As a member of our professional staff cohort, you will be actively involved in working towards our vision of a better world. By supporting the academic endeavour across teaching, research, and the student life, you will have the opportunity to contribute to activities that have a lasting impact on our community.

Join a community where excellence is at the core of our culture, contributions are valued and a range of benefits and rewards are available, such as:

Up to 26 weeks paid parental leave/paid primary care leave
17% superannuation contributions + 17.5% annual leave loading
Access to flexible working
Health and wellness discounts - fitness passport access, free yearly flu vaccinations, discounted health insurance, and access to our Employee Assistance Program for staff and their immediate family
Career development opportunities -access to exclusive internal-only vacancies and our Study for Staff program
On campus childcare options
Affordable parking (from just $6.40 a day)
Salary packaging options
About You

You are a self-motivated, solutions focused Software Engineer with excellent communication skills. You will also demonstrate:

Qualifications and training equivalent to an undergraduate degree in IT or related field and subsequent relevant experience; or an equivalent combination of relevant experience and/or education/training.
Comfortable working across a range of programming languages including Python, R and MATLAB.
Demonstrated experience encoding a workflow in at least one of the above languages.
Experience using high-performance computing.
Strong interpersonal and communication skills with proven ability to produce clear, succinct documentation.
Demonstrated experience working collaboratively with a team.
Strong problem-solving skills with the ability to plan, prioritize tasks, meet deadlines, and work adaptably both independently and in a team.

Desirable

Knowledge of cloud services
Familiarity with relational database management systems
Docker and container-based development.
Prior experience with laboratory information management systems.
Strong mathematical background.

The successful candidate may be required to complete a number of pre-employment checks, including: right to work in Australia, conduct concerning gender-based violence, criminal check, education check etc.

You must maintain unrestricted work rights in Australia for the duration of this appointment to apply. Employer sponsored work rights are not available for this appointment.

Questions?

For more information about this opportunity, please contact Dr Tim McCubbin - t.mccubbin@uq.edu.au

For application inquiries, please reach out to the Talent Acquisition team at talent@uq.edu.au, stating the job reference number (below) in the subject line.

Resume

Our strength as an institution lies in our diverse colleagues. We're dedicated to equity, diversity, and inclusion, fostering an environment that mirrors our wider community. We're committed to attracting, retaining, and promoting diverse talent. Alice/AI is building the platform that gives SME owners back 15+ hours per week by automating the operational work that currently lives across disconnected tools (email, calendars, files, CRM/accounting). We've built the core agentic AI engine and now we're entering a critical phase: architectural hardening, security uplift, and deep integrations into the systems our customers live in every day.

If you're a senior, hands-on engineer who enjoys turning a promising platform into a production-ready system—and you're open to a startup-style package (lower cash, higher upside via equity)—we'd love to talk.

What you'll do (high impact, hands-on)

You'll operate as a CTO/Lean Engineering Lead: with a product focus, making pragmatic decisions, shipping core foundations, and setting us up to scale.

1) Architecture & security hardening (first 4–8 weeks)

Review current platform architecture for scalability, maintainability and reliability

Identify and mitigate priority security risks (auth, tenancy/data isolation, API security, secrets management, audit/logging)

Produce and execute a practical roadmap for improvement (12–18 month horizon, MVP-first)

2) Build core product integrations (our MCP foundation)

Own end-to-end integrations including OAuth, sync logic, rate limits, retries, observability and data modelling:

Google Workspace: Gmail, Calendar, Drive

Microsoft 365: Outlook, Calendar, OneDrive

Xero: invoices, contacts, cashflow basics

3) Evolve the core platform

Strengthen backend services and APIs (Java) and work closely with the AI orchestration layer (Python with LangChain/LangGraph)

Improve data pipelines that feed our agents and enable reliable automation

Establish pragmatic engineering practices (CI/CD, test strategy, release hygiene, monitoring)

Our stack

Cloud: AWS (Australia region)

Backend: Java

Frontend: React Native

AI Orchestration: Python, LangChain, LangGraph

LLM integrations: OpenAI API, Google Vertex AI, Groq, AWS Bedrock

What we're looking for
Must-haves

Strong senior experience building and shipping backend/platform systems (ideally Java)

Ideally 7-8 years of experience in backend/platform systems development

Proven experience integrating with third-party SaaS APIs and managing OAuth flows in production

Practical cloud security mindset (AWS, IAM, auth patterns, API security, data isolation/tenancy)

Comfortable collaborating across Java + Python systems

High ownership: you don't just identify problems—you ship fixes

Australian work rights will be considered on a case-by-case basis for this remote/hybrid position.

Nice-to-haves

Experience with SMEs, vertical SaaS, or workflow automation products

Familiarity with agentic AI patterns, LLM tooling, or ML-adjacent product development

Exposure to compliance/security baselines (SOC2-style controls, even if informal)

Why join

Real product, real users, real mission (SMEs are under-served and drowning in admin)

Fully funded with runway to build properly (not "week-to-week survival")

Meaningful equity and the chance to shape the technical direction from here

Work on a modern AI stack with practical constraints (security, reliability, integrations)

About the compensation (transparent)

This role is not Big Tech cash. We're offering a below-market salary balanced by meaningful equity because we're optimising for long-term upside and impact. We'll share the band and equity range with candidates who reach first interview, and we're happy to discuss structuring (e.g., contract-to-perm, milestone-based increases).
